	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655711920876>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655711920876>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655711920876>Pets and EXPerience</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655711920876#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 8:05 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=450><span id=Sage>Sparr</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>113 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If a single pet outdamages all the other people who did damage to something it will take its share of the experience as if it was an even member of the winning group.&nbsp;&nbsp;This means if you are soloing then you need to outdamage your pet or it will take half the experience on each kill.  When grouped this isnt really a problem as any decent group will always outdamage a single pet.  When grouped with multiple pets its even better because if two pets do even damage then all the caster has to do is 1 damage so that neither pet outdamaged everyone else (including the other pet).<br><br>PS: Im posting this in all the pet class forums</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul>
</td></ul></tr></table>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655495023768>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655495023768>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655495023768>CHA or INT?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655495023768#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 7:29 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=380><span id=Scholar>Cubwynn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>67 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I know that most guides say that INT is the most important stat for you to be concerned with when creating an Enchanter. Personally, I believe that if you spend most of your point on CHA, you can free up a lot of inventory slots for the more potent INT items (instead of CHA items). Just a thought... discuss!<br><br>Cubwynn<br>Lanys T'vyl&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>3 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9692695635538>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=9692695635538>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9692695635538>RE: CHA or INT?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9692695635538#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 5:32 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1606><span id= >Boueff</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'd suggest putting more into INT originally myself. It's a lot easier to get larger CHA boosts earlier. For instance, you can add +28 CHA using 2 Elec Star Ruby Rings and 2 Gold Cat Eye Bracers.<br><br>Lots harder to add 28 INT using 2 rings and bracers.<br><br>However, do not neglect your CHA either. More mana isn't important if you can't get your mind spells to stick.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br>Boueff Fhro'mahjj (33 MAG)<br>Arusab (51 ENC)<br>And a host of others<br>The CommuneXegony</td></td></tr>
