	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=9678437723966>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9678437723966>RE: CHA or INT?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9678437723966#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Sep 1st 5:29 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1229><span id= >Tashim</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I find that AC, Int, and Cha are all very important.<br>However, there aren't very many items that provide AC *and* Cha.<br>But, there are quite a few that provide AC *and* Int.<br><br>I generally recommend a good mix of the three.&nbsp;&nbsp;Myself, I tend to have Int items to start with, but as I get lower in mana, I swap out to wear charisma gear (since, I've already used the mana that the extra int provided.)  This allows my charisma-based spells to be more effective as I get lower in mana.<br>If you don't like to swap out equipment in the middle of fights, (timing is everything, and missing an important detail can mean the difference between victory or defeat) then I would suggest using Int gear when meding, and buffing, but wear Charisma gear when you need get ready to fight (if you're doing crowd control, which *should* be often.)<br><br>Just remember:  All the intelligence and charisma in the world ain't gonna do a dead enchanter any good.</p>&nbsp;<br>Tashim, 65th Enchanter<br>Blood of the Spider</td></td></tr>
