	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=96654141424667>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96654141424667>Soloing an Enchanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96654141424667#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 3:43 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Soloing Enchanters is somewhat difficult. You must have a higher level Character get Trade/Droppable items to give to a Level 1 Enchanter. After you get the Enchanter to about Level 12 he will be easy to solo in "Some" Zones. One of the zones he is easiest to solo in is WC where he can charm a Willowisp (Can only be hit with Magic) To fight whatever he wants it to fight. Seeing as willowisps are green at level 12 He shouldnt do much harm when charm wears off. If you cant get the spell off make sure you have sow and run about 200feet ahead then cast the spell. As soon as it is recharmed go back to fighting. But i know what your thinking there isnt much to fight in WC so... Go to North Karana there are willowisps there also although maybe a little scarce. Turn invisable then go off searching for a Willowisp. Be sure to shout and ask if any Hill Giants are up before you do this though. After you've found the willowisp Charm it and go off to Find something that cons Black or Yellow that cant use any form of magical attack. But never ever fight a Highland Lion as an Enchanter Youll be killed before you get to the guards they are as fast as sow. Most of the time this is an Excellent strategy and is used by many Enchanters. So in conclusion there is a very easy way to solo Enchanters if you have a Higher Level Character. I got most of The Experience to get my Enchanter to level 12 From Legionnaire Shoulderpads from Crushbone. Also Enchanters Are Excellent Jewel Crafters so put all your points after level 4 into Jewel Craft until it wont let you. Silver Star Ruby Veils go for around 200-300pp on The Rathe server just as a Perspective on how Profitable an Enchanter can be. The Enchant Silver spell you get at level 8. It is very useful and almost all Enchanters buy the spell. I have already made 500pp using this spell and my skill in Jewel Craft alone. Some things that drop jewels so you dont have to buy them are... Griffawns, Earth Elementals, Minotaur Guards, Emerald Drakes, And any High Level MoBs. On the Earth Elemental's it is a rare drop so if you go there be prepared for a lot of killing. And Minotaur Guards are around level 26-29 so dont expect to get Jewels from them at level 8 :)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Also one of the most useful spells ive had for duels and when i got in trouble is Fear. If you buy any spell at level 4 buy Fear.<br>     But the most usefull spell of all is all your illusions and Alliance and the higher forms of it. With those spells you can go anywhere and do any quest with those spells. At Level 12 You could go into Neriak and go to the Wizard, Mage, Enchanter Guild and do any of their quests. <br>     And i think that the Enchanter is second in Dueling only to the Necromancer. One of the Best spells vs. another caster is Eye of Confusion. It blinds them so they cannot cast a spell unless they've Memorized where everything that was on their screen. After you do that Cast a DoT then a DD until it wears off (Make sure you run out of their sight Before You Cast DD spells.) Cast a Fear spell and let your pet go at it. Med while your target is Feared When it wears off get up and go somewhere where they cannot see you casting and Just Do Direct Damage spells over and over until they die :)<br>        Hope this helped everyone.<br> <br>        <br>                       Signed,<br>                      Alfasteir</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
